<p style="color: #666; font-size: 14px;">March 23, 2026</p>
<hr>
<h2>Tech Earnings Recap</h2>
<p>It was a big week for tech earnings. Here's what you need to know:</p>
<p>Apple reported Q2 revenue of $98.5B, beating estimates by $2.1B. iPhone revenue was flat but Services hit an all-time high at $26.3B. Tim Cook said AI features drove record upgrade rates in emerging markets.</p>
<p>Microsoft posted $65.2B in revenue, up 14% YoY. Azure grew 29%, slightly below the 31% analysts expected. Satya Nadella emphasized that Copilot adoption crossed 100M weekly active users.</p>
<h2>AI Regulation Update</h2>
<p>The EU AI Act enforcement begins next month. Companies have until April 15 to register high-risk AI systems. The big question: how strictly will "general purpose AI" be interpreted?</p>
